This paper is about improving the efficiency of a search engine ranking system for e-commerce, which involves using machine learning techniques to select a subset of effective factors for each search instance. The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for image factor extraction, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning for solving a combinatorial optimization problem, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, the main focus of the paper is on improving the efficiency and effectiveness of search engine ranking, which suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of supervised and unsupervised methods for feature selection, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Overall, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
